# Frontend design workflow

When designing, building, redesigning, or polishing any frontend UI in this project, follow this pipeline in order. Do not skip steps.

Also apply this rule when the user asks for UI/UX work even if no frontend file is open.

## Stack context

- Next.js 13 (Pages Router), React 18, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion (`lib/motion.js` spring tokens)
- Custom CSS variables and components in `styles/globals.css` — no shadcn/ui unless explicitly added
- Adapt all generated code to existing patterns (`card`, `glass-panel`, `soft-button`, `CozyRoomIllustration`, etc.)
- Use skeleton loading (`components/Skeleton.js`) instead of spinners for all data-fetching UI

---

## Step 1b — Framer Motion (animation layer)

1. Import motion tokens from `lib/motion.js` (`spring`, `stagger`, `hoverGlow`, `pageTransition`).
2. Use soft entrance animations (`opacity`, `y`, subtle `scale`, optional `blur`).
3. Add gentle hover/tap feedback on interactive elements; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
4. Use `AnimatePresence` for lists, modals, and page transitions.

---

## Step 1 — ui-ux-pro-max (design system first)

1. Read `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` before writing UI code.
2. Run a design-system search from the project root:

```bash
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product type> <style keywords> <industry>" --design-system -p "Heartstrings Club" --stack nextjs
```

3. Use `--persist` when starting a major redesign so rules land in `design-system/MASTER.md`.
4. Supplement with domain searches (`--domain ux`, `--domain typography`, `--domain style`) when needed.

If Python is missing, tell the user to install it, then continue using the skill's written guidelines from `SKILL.md`.

---

## Step 2 — 21st.dev Magic MCP (component generation)

Use the **Magic MCP** server for new or complex UI components (cards, nav, forms, hero sections, modals).

1. Read the tool schema under `mcps/user-Magic_MCP/tools/` before calling.
2. Prefer these tools:
   - `21st_magic_component_inspiration` — browse/reference patterns first
   - `21st_magic_component_builder` — generate new components
   - `21st_magic_component_refiner` — improve existing components
   - `logo_search` — brand logos only when needed
3. After MCP returns a snippet, integrate it into `components/` or `pages/` and adapt styling to this project's warm hand-drawn design system.
4. Do not paste 21st output verbatim if it conflicts with project tokens, fonts (Manrope + Cormorant Garamond), or custom illustration style.

---

## Step 3 — impeccable (polish and critique)

1. Read `.cursor/skills/impeccable/SKILL.md` before finalizing UI.
2. Load project context (requires `PRODUCT.md` and `DESIGN.md` at project root):

```bash
node .cursor/skills/impeccable/scripts/load-context.mjs
```

3. Apply relevant impeccable references for the task (`craft.md`, `polish.md`, `motion-design.md`, `color-and-contrast.md`, `interaction-design.md`, `critique.md`, etc.).
4. Use pinned shortcuts when appropriate: `/critique`, `/polish`, `/document`.
5. Before marking UI work complete, self-review against impeccable: hierarchy, spacing, contrast, motion, cognitive load, responsive behavior, and UX copy.

---

## Completion checklist

- [ ] ui-ux-pro-max design system consulted (script run or SKILL.md applied)
- [ ] New/complex components went through 21st.dev Magic MCP when appropriate
- [ ] impeccable critique applied; visual and UX issues addressed
- [ ] Code matches project conventions; no emoji icons; hover/focus states present
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected for animations
